                                </p></note></person><person><persName>Adolf Eichmann</persName><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000564"/></linkGrp><note><p>German SS officer in charge of “Jewish affairs” at the Security Service from 1935. From 1941 he was the head of the Jewish Affairs Department of the Reich Security Main Office and he was in charge of deportations from various European destinations to ghettos and death camps. In March 1944 he arrived in Budapest with his special unit and they arranged the ghettoization and deportation of the Hungarian Jews. After the war he fled to Argentina. Israeli agents abducted him in 1960 and took him to Jerusalem, where he was tried and he was executed in 1962. </p></note></person><person xml:id="ehri_ts_gelbart_isidor"><persName>Gelbart, Yisrael (Isidor)</persName><note><p>Holocaust survivor.
                            </p></note></person><person xml:id="ehri_ts_muller_cyla"><persName>Muller (Wiesenthal), Cyla</persName><note><p>Holocaust survivor from Galicia. She married Simon Wiesenthal in 1936.</p></note></person></listPerson><listPlace><place xml:id="EHRI-TS-19600724-A_6"><placeName>no place</placeName><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="#EHRI-TS-19600724-A_6"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Munich</placeName><location><geo>48.13743 11.57549</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/2867714/munich.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Munich"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Buchach</placeName><location><geo>49.06234 25.39496</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/711348/buchach.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buchach"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Cleveland</placeName><location><geo>41.4995 -81.69541</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="http://www.geonames.org/5150529/cleveland.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cleveland"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Ohio</placeName><location><geo>41.55753 -89.46093</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/4904612/ohio.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ohio%2C_Illinois"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Saarbrücken</placeName><location><geo>49.23262 7.00982</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/2842647/saarbruecken.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saarbr%C3%BCcken"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Chortkiv</placeName><location><geo>49.01701 25.79808</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/710400/chortkiv.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chortkiv"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Borshchiv</placeName><location><geo>48.80319 26.03171</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/711587/borshchiv.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borshchiv"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Yahilnytsia</placeName><location><geo>48.94145 25.749</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/688602/yahilnytsia.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yahilnytsia"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Germany</placeName><location><geo>51.5 10.5</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Lviv</placeName><location><geo>49.83826 24.02324</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/702550/lviv.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lviv"/></linkGrp></place><place><placeName>Warsaw</placeName><location><geo>52.22977 21.01178</geo></location><linkGrp><link type="normal" target="https://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html"/><link type="desc" target="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warsaw"/></linkGrp></place></listPlace></sourceDesc>
